=Generate a discount plan using the following inputs:

Discount Type: {{ $json.discount_type }}
Percentage Value: {{ $json.percentage_value }}
Fixed Amount: {{ $json.fixed_value }}
Country: {{ $json.country }}
purchase price : {{ $json.purchase_price }}
product stock : {{ $json.product_stock }}
Trigger Type: {{ $json.trigger_type }}
Minimum Order Amount: {{ $json.order_amount }}
Customer Type: {{ $json.customer_type }}

IMPORTANT — How to handle null values:
- Any field showing "null" means the user did not select or provide that value. Completely ignore null fields — do not mention them, do not reference them, and do not treat them as relevant to the plan.
- Only use the fields that contain actual values.
- If {{ $json.discount_type }} is "percentage", use {{ $json.percentage_value }} as the discount. Ignore {{ $json.fixed_value }}.
- If {{ $json.discount_type }} is "fixed", use {{ $json.fixed_value }} as the discount. Ignore {{ $json.percentage_value }}.
- If {{ $json.trigger_type }} is "order_amount", use {{ $json.order_amount }} as the trigger threshold. Ignore {{ $json.customer_type }}.
- If {{ $json.trigger_type }} is "customer_type", use {{ $json.customer_type }} as the trigger. Ignore {{ $json.order_amount }}.
- If {{ $json.country }} is not null, include it as the target market context of the plan.

